<paragraph id="9F5E4780C4B660B57D277197F7D29A02" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="EF3A6D8D90390A9A53847E9B85FECD3B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8E8C52DD3303D7C39238FAFE0008A55A" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Distribution of S. cordatum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689708" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">15</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2AC604C8F565461F2020039077645AEA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="72474250039D92EE99BB0EFD322B1B8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs from northeastern Africa and the Arabian Peninsula to Pakistan and western India (Punjab, Gujarat, Maharashtra). The record of 
<taxonomicName id="C4CB422A3635F6F81861C0646091DF5B" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="E58AC28B3702E9627A470807F05EF41D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Tamil Nadu (
<bibRefCitation id="06E073D2169B0ADA2BA7DF8526DAE6A7" author="Ramachandran, A" journalOrPublisher="Rheedea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="56 - 58" refId="B202" refString="Ramachandran, A, Viswanathan, MB, 2010. Solanum cordatum (Solanaceae) - a new record to southern India. Rheedea 20: 56 - 58" title="Solanum cordatum (Solanaceae) - a new record to southern India." volume="20" year="2010">Ramachandran and Viswanathan 2010</bibRefCitation>
) is based on mis-identified specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="3E8218CDFB6491729EF1834E4050BA9C" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. wightii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="wightii">
<emphasis id="8033E4C8BEEED18A8772433BF42A2CCD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. wightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C22B5375D953DCE265F99B51317F1D79" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="D7196AC576D5272CF8E41F8F372A400D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EAF81AE5C00A5F8E66B5556D9135331" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="47363127AFB4B5989E4EFB85C382173A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="895A24904C7C1A2BCD7FCF6E5968F27E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in grassland, bushland, and open woodland on silty, sandy, or stony soil; low elevations (not recorded for India, from sea level to 1,500 m fide 
<bibRefCitation id="B69ECF54A7D1436FFCD55B5AB653BF3C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 428" refId="B259" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016. A revision of the &quot;spiny solanums,&quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar. Systematic Botany Monographs 99: 1 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" title="A revision of the &quot; spiny solanums, &quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" volume="99" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D2E386E2873038D7C189AEDCAF2DB71" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="common names and uses">
<paragraph id="D83CB4DB423682DD6DCA396F67666375" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Common names and uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F190FAA43A62A7ED73C9A942891B748" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
None recorded from the region (see 
<bibRefCitation id="E8A951245F0226922C6E0E5C380F8121" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 428" refId="B259" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016. A revision of the &quot;spiny solanums,&quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar. Systematic Botany Monographs 99: 1 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" title="A revision of the &quot; spiny solanums, &quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" volume="99" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp 2016</bibRefCitation>
for Africa).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="823CB7DD4E8DF8ADF0E546680588EFE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="962654DBC84177A805B49733F65446A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conservation status</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F4DB87061A82ED17B865BF8AEE59196" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="742461CF13E18CD100DE1C5DDCA5724E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation id="D8D12F87C72858B42DC72330D220209C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2021-1.RLTS.T186619213A186619254.en" author="Knapp, S" journalOrPublisher="Anales del Jardin Botanico de Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B125" refString="Knapp, S, 2021a. Solanum cordatum. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2021: e.T186619213A186619254. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2021-1.RLTS.T186619213A186619254.en" title="Solanum cordatum. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2021: e. T 186619213 A 186619254." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2021-1.RLTS.T186619213A186619254.en" year="2021 a">Knapp 2021a</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="12F9E7BFB254F5F7D0FC7C1BE650D77B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="057CE3482C5C71E0FFA60DD4DABAEE56" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been formally assessed as a species of Least Concern (LC; https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/186619213/186619254).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F3315E69786401507403F6EFDF587056" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="325F7A4481DFA39C50E21FBF119EC3A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4889F549E963D3CA0662DA7538D9BE21" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="BAB8DFE8CB5E4CED1E11D46D0C75D768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="049E96D763762EF1EE31A5BBE66320D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be much less commonly collected in western India than is the very similar and sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="8E4579843D3B8BD9ADD60653BE4AEA59" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="0DEFD504AC10C9741DCFD4D74CE9D6CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="640352C26FAA27640EEFD197386D2C2B" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="CBEDCA5AD70EE5FBF3E22415967928BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its compact multangulate stem pubescence of trichomes with many very short (&lt;0.1 mm long) rays, 
<taxonomicName id="084B87A24BD9060F246C37EE363D952F" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="C11BAAFB366E50A37E0A8C02BD0F4957" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has porrect-stellate trichomes with fewer rays that are marginally longer (&gt; 0.15 mm long); stems of 
<taxonomicName id="D4E5484C6D467F8C79AA20A1F848852D" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="D522422F8892D2E69C07F1F095C4C9EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear white dotted from the stubby trichomes. Leaf petioles of 
<taxonomicName id="8D3DB9C6B98779C2682D525D4EB66E82" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="0BC976D5C8C7FA57EC4F4189DFFBCB31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are decurrent and narrowly winged, while leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="DF9E17A6A5102ECF3278BE0820B4BA44" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="40F0F0D80CD268670DAEB76431874745" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinctly petiolate. The calyx lobes of 
<taxonomicName id="0B6C96BFA5041C0993EB9A8FF0DF6564" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="698A5F9FEF7A2B29B5D7DC913FD9F476" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are longer and narrower than those of 
<taxonomicName id="2C5F88DC4DFB9A004598D1BCDEABD6D0" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="D995E17E080E9F0F1D07B33206294131" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while anthers are shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="AABE41689FCA9D81F8213E03A4D06E94" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="0F1A0C2BEEF659B23E999407489DE8E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(3-5 mm versus 4.5-7 mm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="821F162D4F369D8F6EA33D03F476A1D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In eastern Africa, 
<taxonomicName id="E12F60A7116FB7368A2D940C9EDFEA94" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="50933B27FE5321984290395B14B34DFD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deciduous in the dry season, growing opportunistically during times of moisture (
<bibRefCitation id="83EEFEE75748BA8F0633FD088ECED8BA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 428" refId="B259" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016. A revision of the &quot;spiny solanums,&quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar. Systematic Botany Monographs 99: 1 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" title="A revision of the &quot; spiny solanums, &quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" volume="99" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp 2016</bibRefCitation>
). This may be part of the reason for its relatively fewer collections in India than 
<taxonomicName id="8BB74FBCBF269A1BA1B5473FF77C4879" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="7A9EC8652552A4E835CD8FAC675BFAF6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this species has more robust leaves that are not deciduous. 
<bibRefCitation id="96D9B4A64D78ABD9F689A4558EF3E61C" author="Wood, JRI" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B273" refString="Wood, JRI, 1997. A handbook of the Yemen flora. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." title="A handbook of the Yemen flora. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." year="1997">Wood (1997)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="3E050027E9D6D5C862F4D05A2CE505CE" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="EE4A0E3DC89DE4D1025A3646A1E9044C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was an &quot;Indian species which extends west to Yemen but is only found in Africa in Somalia.&quot; It is indeed found only in the Horn of Africa (Somalia, Ethiopia, and northern Kenya).
</paragraph>
<caption id="66921BCA8FEF24ED104FA36176A8FA1F" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689708" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 15" startId="F15">
<paragraph id="A1858F1AD74A7BD266DBF80B006B495F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="627E3940A2AB539B4C1904C8EE441958" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 15.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="FD347A68A58CDC6A8EF1A277383F8696" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="9FA79343E8F8535350E02B2F0C8FB9EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="FF1B661D969F28FDDADDE3810490415F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="ED09D0C51681B60FF5D0FC527E750BB1" author="Ramachandran, A" journalOrPublisher="Rheedea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="56 - 58" refId="B202" refString="Ramachandran, A, Viswanathan, MB, 2010. Solanum cordatum (Solanaceae) - a new record to southern India. Rheedea 20: 56 - 58" title="Solanum cordatum (Solanaceae) - a new record to southern India." volume="20" year="2010">Ramachandran and Viswanathan (2010)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="6E500F9C73361B772D660C85A9D1B10E" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="4DD71386D20A4C0378A6C00841530520" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sethukadai in the Namakkal District of Tamil Nadu, far from its known range in India. This report is based on mis-identified specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="86C461AA361F98F6D367F406E8779D7A" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. wightii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="wightii">
<emphasis id="3983822C2D9484BD7BBB3F13F71D3A0A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. wightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the description in 
<bibRefCitation id="3A371964F3A687E05A51AF6B3DB43607" author="Ramachandran, A" journalOrPublisher="Rheedea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="56 - 58" refId="B202" refString="Ramachandran, A, Viswanathan, MB, 2010. Solanum cordatum (Solanaceae) - a new record to southern India. Rheedea 20: 56 - 58" title="Solanum cordatum (Solanaceae) - a new record to southern India." volume="20" year="2010">Ramachandran and Viswanathan (2010)</bibRefCitation>
appears to be a mixture of elements from published descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="2C33A5395F872E29EAAA0FA87A492608" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="7C4BC8ACD6C5DB19F887848B87F552F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the actual specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="2BDC38A569D844B91B9C7D3D46CB6F4A" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. wightii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="wightii">
<emphasis id="1D2726BFF9E12478B2CE636AE8652915" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. wightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they used as their new record.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
